{{Understanding Scientific Terms}} ==Lesson 3 - Common Prefixes ==
====prefixes==== : '''end/o-''' : inside, inner : '''ex/o-''' : from, out of : '''ecto-''' : outside, outer : '''epi-''' : over, upon : '''peri-''' : around : '''proto-''' : before : ''' pro-''' : before : '''hypo-''' : below, under, less : '''hyper-''' : above, excessive, more : '''ab''' : from, away from : '''ad''' : toward, to : '''micro''' : small : '''macro''' : big
====root====
: '''derm''' : skin
{{Latin/Exercise|Define the word| # epidermis # hypodermic | # The skin found on the top of an organism. # Pertaining to something below the skin. }}
How would you write the words with these meanings? {{Latin/Exercise|Write the word| # The skin on the inside of an organism. # Someone who is more active than is normal. | # endoderm # hyperactive }}

