== Discussion ==
{{auto navigation|CSS tables|Calculator}} {{auto category}}
Thanks for posting this interesting example. For self education, I tried to get this actually running with xsltforms. After fixing many many syntax errors caused by the wiki's presentation, I could not locate the external schema. Would it be possible for the original contributor to provide a downloadable copy of the plain text xml sources which includes the referenced schema file named "CreateReport.xform.xsd"?

{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Patronus| type=Magical term| features=Names effect of [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Expecto Patronum|Expecto Patronum]] spell| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Prisoner of Azkaban|''Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban'']]}}
== Overview ==
A '''''Patronus''''' is the visible result of the casting of the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Expecto Patronum|Expecto Patronum]] spell. By extension, it is also used to refer to the spell itself.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
When the Expecto Patronum spell is cast, the result is an apparent object made of white vapour. This object, the Patronus, often takes the shape of an animal; [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]]'s, for instance, is a stag. The animal in question often has some relationship to the person casting it: for instance, [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Albus Dumbledore|Dumbledore]]'s is a phoenix, which seems to fit him well given his choice of pet, and Harry's takes the shape that his father took as an [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Animagus|Animagus]]. Dumbledore has also devised a way of allowing a patronus to carry messages. More information is available at [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Expecto Patronum|Expecto Patronum]].
